<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/119786992-shrimpy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1597244376i/119786992._UY100_CR41,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/119786992-shrimpy">Shrimpy</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The rights to a movie have been purchased. I personally don&apos;t want them to make any film-related adaptations of this series. Let the books and the Lad<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The rights to a movie have been purchased. I personally don't want them to make any film-related adaptations of this series. Let the books and the Lady Anne rest in peace please! But as with other book-to-movie adaptions *cough cough* Eragon *cough*, Hollywood tends to ruin fantasy series movies, unless they're done very skillfully and they keep close to the books.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
