        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer25248422" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5284480524614758119">I enjoyed the first book very much. While I enjoyed the other two, I felt the writing reverted to the &quot;he said, she said&quot; of other follow-on fantasy novels (any number of David Eddings books qualify). The world of Pern is novel and the dragon/rider relationship is intriguing to read about. It&apos;s a worthwhile read, but I don&apos;t feel the full potential was achieved due to a lack of depth and more telling than showing.</span>
  <span id="freeText5284480524614758119" style="display:none">I enjoyed the first book very much. While I enjoyed the other two, I felt the writing reverted to the "he said, she said" of other follow-on fantasy novels (any number of David Eddings books qualify). The world of Pern is novel and the dragon/rider relationship is intriguing to read about. It's a worthwhile read, but I don't feel the full potential was achieved due to a lack of depth and more telling than showing.</span>
